      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This answer does not make sense to me. If the intent of <code>Optional.of()</code> is to throw a <code>NullPointerException</code> and fail early, is using <code>@NonNull</code>, <code>Validate.notNull</code>, etc not a better choice? or even just doing a direct check: <code>if (foobar != null) throw new NPE()</code>. If the value of Optional is never going to be none then in this case is it not misleading to still call it an Optional?"
