      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@MarioFusco Because there might be multiple such specific situations in the same logic, and not all are present. eg, <code>if (condition) { return Optional.of(f()); } else { Optional.empty(); }</code>, where <code>f()</code> should never return null. Using <code>ofNullable</code> would hide errors when <code>f</code> does return null erroneously."
